        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 4:32PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 432 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 12
miles northeast of Siler City, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Durham, Chapel Hill, Hillsborough, Carrboro, Sutphin, Cane Creek
Reservoir, Saxapahaw, Eno River State Park, and Jordan Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
